1
00:00:07,007 --> 00:00:09,726
Milica!

2
00:00:10,087 --> 00:00:13,762
I'll go bankrupt!

3
00:00:14,447 --> 00:00:18,201
I can't carry these anymore.

4
00:00:18,687 --> 00:00:21,724
BOSNIA 1992

5
00:00:35,167 --> 00:00:38,603
Milica!

6
00:01:15,767 --> 00:01:18,964
Out of the way!

7
00:02:04,607 --> 00:02:07,075
1, 2, 3, 4...

8
00:02:17,247 --> 00:02:20,205
Let's see if your old man still
has it!

9
00:02:30,727 --> 00:02:33,799
Milos, you have to play with
your head.

10
00:02:33,887 --> 00:02:36,162
Yeah, right! Piss off!

11
00:02:45,767 --> 00:02:48,679
Hey, Eso!

12
00:03:04,047 --> 00:03:06,845
Hey, Luka, you can't be in two
places

13
00:03:06,927 --> 00:03:09,885
at the same time. - Sure, I can!

14
00:03:14,207 --> 00:03:16,163
You see, I can!

15
00:03:25,207 --> 00:03:27,596
Lord! I hope he remembers me.

16
00:03:27,687 --> 00:03:31,123
Hey, Einstein, the coach
has a memory for remembering.

17
00:03:31,287 --> 00:03:32,686
For remembering?

18
00:03:33,927 --> 00:03:36,964
It's been 18 months since we
left Belgrad

19
00:03:37,047 --> 00:03:41,598
Just keep your mind on the match.
Your job's to play.

20
00:03:51,887 --> 00:03:55,277
Hey, Veljo...
My great big friend!

21
00:03:55,367 --> 00:03:57,517
Here's your pension.

22
00:03:57,607 --> 00:03:59,598
I'm glad to see you!

23
00:04:05,887 --> 00:04:07,559
Amazing...

24
00:04:08,287 --> 00:04:10,084
The miracle of life!

25
00:04:13,207 --> 00:04:14,720
Neighbor!

26
00:04:15,207 --> 00:04:16,799
Neighbor!

27
00:04:28,567 --> 00:04:31,035
Joksa! Hey, Joksa!

28
00:04:31,127 --> 00:04:33,595
You're too small to scare me...

29
00:05:22,127 --> 00:05:26,405
Get that donkey off the track,
Vujan!

30
00:05:26,487 --> 00:05:29,206
I'll go bankrupt, my dear Veljo.

31
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:33,565
These are in great demand
and that cow won't carry them.

32
00:05:33,647 --> 00:05:35,683
Why not? - She's suffering.

33
00:05:35,767 --> 00:05:40,602
Can't she suffer in a ditch?
What's it matter where she suffers?

34
00:05:40,847 --> 00:05:42,803
I'll have to use...

35
00:05:44,407 --> 00:05:45,476
a stick.

36
00:05:46,367 --> 00:05:50,679
Get a move on!
You won't get in my way.

37
00:05:52,527 --> 00:05:55,678
What's this? Why is she crying?

38
00:05:55,767 --> 00:05:59,237
She's lovesick.
She wants a train to run her over.

39
00:05:59,327 --> 00:06:02,842
What train? The track isn't
finished yet.

40
00:06:02,927 --> 00:06:06,317
Exactly what I told her.

41
00:06:06,567 --> 00:06:09,639
I'll use the stick on her. - A
stick?

42
00:06:09,767 --> 00:06:11,723
I'm skeptical about that.

43
00:06:11,807 --> 00:06:15,959
People! They've killed Joksa!

44
00:06:25,487 --> 00:06:26,602
Luka!

45
00:06:27,687 --> 00:06:29,643
I have to tell you something!

46
00:06:32,047 --> 00:06:33,765
Just let me get past.

47
00:06:38,127 --> 00:06:40,118
I have to tell you...

48
00:06:44,247 --> 00:06:45,646
Just one word!

49
00:06:58,127 --> 00:07:02,245
The bears are slaughtering everybody!
But Tito shot the last one.

50
00:07:02,327 --> 00:07:04,602
They're pouring in from Croatia.

51
00:07:04,727 --> 00:07:08,436
Beasts from Croatia!
And you just sit here playing!

52
00:07:08,527 --> 00:07:11,599
What beasts?
Why, bears!

53
00:07:14,247 --> 00:07:17,319
They're like ours, only
different.

54
00:07:17,407 --> 00:07:22,845
A bit bigger but with gray fur.
They must be Persian bears.

55
00:07:22,927 --> 00:07:26,920
Not Persian bears!
They're fleeing the war in Croatia.

56
00:07:27,047 --> 00:07:29,766
Is the track OK? - Why shouldn't
it be?

57
00:07:29,847 --> 00:07:32,202
Luka, this is no joke.

58
00:07:32,287 --> 00:07:35,597
Folks are dying and you sit
here playing.

59
00:07:50,367 --> 00:07:52,483
Here, boy!

60
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:55,083
Here, boy!

61
00:07:55,967 --> 00:07:57,036
Radovan!

62
00:07:58,647 --> 00:08:00,160
What's up?

63
00:08:02,247 --> 00:08:06,081
Why won't she leave me alone?

64
00:08:06,287 --> 00:08:07,800
What is it?

65
00:08:07,887 --> 00:08:11,436
Let's stop so I can feed the dog.
Be a darling.

66
00:08:11,527 --> 00:08:15,600
Since when does a goddam mayor
feed stray dogs?

67
00:08:15,727 --> 00:08:17,638
Tell me that.

68
00:08:18,167 --> 00:08:19,759
Since when does a mayor

69
00:08:19,847 --> 00:08:23,556
gobble breakfast in a car?

70
00:08:24,607 --> 00:08:27,724
Can't you see that Lily's in
love?

71
00:08:38,007 --> 00:08:41,158
Paws off my lunch!

72
00:08:41,367 --> 00:08:43,039
Good for you!

73
00:08:43,127 --> 00:08:44,924
Scram!

74
00:08:52,487 --> 00:08:57,925
You're a lawyer, Filipovic.
We made you party secretary.

75
00:08:58,047 --> 00:09:00,880
You know these things better
than me.

76
00:09:00,967 --> 00:09:04,482
That's why I'm telling you.
There are laws, man.

77
00:09:04,567 --> 00:09:06,683
Want to get us arrested?

78
00:09:06,767 --> 00:09:09,361
Only nitwits get nabbed. - Not
crooks?

79
00:09:09,447 --> 00:09:11,119
That's not what I said.

80
00:09:11,207 --> 00:09:15,325
Yes, it is. Fraud is fraud,
however you dress it up.

81
00:09:15,407 --> 00:09:19,400
But the Muslims & Croats do just the same.
- Do what?

82
00:09:19,487 --> 00:09:22,763
Finance political parties
from cigarettes and oil.

83
00:09:22,847 --> 00:09:25,281
Building democracy on freight
trains!

84
00:09:25,687 --> 00:09:28,838
Tito did it for 30 years. - Tito?

85
00:09:28,927 --> 00:09:32,476
Forget Tito. Tito was Tito,
after all.

86
00:09:49,967 --> 00:09:52,162
I'll tell him everything.

87
00:09:55,687 --> 00:09:58,884
If it isn't my dear old
brother-in-law!

88
00:09:58,967 --> 00:10:01,162
Are we ready for Liberation Day?

89
00:10:01,247 --> 00:10:04,159
The band, not the track.
The Serbians are behind.

90
00:10:04,247 --> 00:10:07,717
But our side is on time.
How are my artists?

91
00:10:08,527 --> 00:10:11,087
My lovely music!

92
00:10:11,207 --> 00:10:13,198
Sir, can I speak to you?

93
00:10:13,287 --> 00:10:15,960
Sparavalo, of the Sarajevo
Opera.

94
00:10:16,047 --> 00:10:18,686
Sarajevo! A magic town.

95
00:10:18,767 --> 00:10:20,723
Mr. Mayor... - Wait!

96
00:10:20,807 --> 00:10:24,277
Mr. Cuhaj, our guest artist from Hungary.
A universal artist.

97
00:10:37,567 --> 00:10:40,559
This is going to be OK.

98
00:10:40,647 --> 00:10:42,683
OK, he says...

99
00:10:42,807 --> 00:10:44,638
As president of the town
council,

100
00:10:44,727 --> 00:10:47,002
I would like to express my
gratitude

101
00:10:47,087 --> 00:10:51,080
for the support you've given
our railroad

102
00:10:51,207 --> 00:10:55,678
But we politicians haven't
slept.

103
00:10:56,047 --> 00:10:58,242
Just read this, bro.

104
00:10:58,327 --> 00:11:04,004
Mr. Mayor, if we don't organize a hunt
the beasts will slaughter us all.

105
00:11:04,087 --> 00:11:07,762
"We approve purchase of a
"Sneider-Holstein locomotive..."

106
00:11:07,847 --> 00:11:09,121
This is fantastic!

107
00:11:09,207 --> 00:11:13,200
Not a single Serb will be left!
Look what you've done!

108
00:11:17,327 --> 00:11:20,558
Mr. Mayor, friends,

109
00:11:20,647 --> 00:11:23,036
allow me to present our project.

110
00:11:23,127 --> 00:11:25,277
Here you see the section of
track that

111
00:11:25,367 --> 00:11:29,042
will link Bosnia and Serbia for
12 miles.

112
00:11:29,127 --> 00:11:31,118
Mr. Mayor... - In fact,

113
00:11:31,207 --> 00:11:35,280
the Austrians first built this track
but then it was destroyed.

114
00:11:35,367 --> 00:11:40,122
We now need to rebuild it
to boost tourism and trade.

115
00:11:40,207 --> 00:11:42,767
With this tunnel... - Mr. Mayor!

116
00:11:43,247 --> 00:11:45,715
...we will overcome a major
obstacle...

117
00:11:46,567 --> 00:11:49,320
and be ready for Liberation Day.

118
00:11:49,407 --> 00:11:51,557
Well done, bro!

119
00:11:51,647 --> 00:11:55,037
We are lumberjacks and we're
okay

120
00:11:55,127 --> 00:11:58,403
In the green forests of Bosni-ay

121
00:11:58,487 --> 00:12:01,877
We are lumberjacks and we're
okay

122
00:12:01,967 --> 00:12:06,199
In the hills and mountains of
Bosni-ay!

123
00:12:07,927 --> 00:12:09,440
Listen, hotshots,

124
00:12:09,527 --> 00:12:11,199
let me tell you the basics

125
00:12:11,287 --> 00:12:13,517
about being a goalie.

126
00:12:13,607 --> 00:12:16,041
I can't wait to hear this!

127
00:12:16,127 --> 00:12:18,163
You have to guard that line

128
00:12:18,247 --> 00:12:21,159
regardless of who's shooting.

129
00:12:21,247 --> 00:12:22,839
Is that so? - You bet.

130
00:12:22,927 --> 00:12:25,760
That's why there are no smart
goalies.

131
00:12:25,927 --> 00:12:30,079
Did Einstein say that?
No, you idiot! Wrong again!

132
00:12:30,167 --> 00:12:32,044
It was the coach who said it.

133
00:12:34,207 --> 00:12:39,964
And now Tomo Krotolina's
gonna show you how to shoot.

134
00:12:49,487 --> 00:12:52,684
Where are you going, for god's
sake!

135
00:12:52,887 --> 00:12:55,196
Didn't you say you're fearless,
goalie?

136
00:12:55,287 --> 00:12:56,959
Then come with me.

137
00:12:57,047 --> 00:12:58,765
What for?

138
00:12:58,887 --> 00:13:02,118
Prove that you're fearless.
- Don't pull!

139
00:13:02,207 --> 00:13:03,606
Who's pulling, Mr. Fearless?

140
00:13:03,687 --> 00:13:05,166
But I wanted to go dancing...

141
00:13:05,247 --> 00:13:07,283
No more buts, Eso.

142
00:13:07,367 --> 00:13:09,005
Here comes a goal shot.

143
00:13:10,767 --> 00:13:13,964
You said you're fearless.

144
00:13:16,847 --> 00:13:19,566
What's all this? - Just stand
there!

145
00:13:20,847 --> 00:13:22,838
No, bro, stand there!

146
00:13:22,967 --> 00:13:26,801
You said you're fearless, so
stand still.

147
00:13:28,807 --> 00:13:31,560
Milos Djukic!

148
00:13:32,047 --> 00:13:34,720
Milos!
Come and see our Eso!

149
00:13:36,487 --> 00:13:38,876
Here's a cross shot.

150
00:13:38,967 --> 00:13:40,878
Catch!

151
00:13:40,967 --> 00:13:43,640
Bravo, boss! Bravo, legend!

152
00:13:43,727 --> 00:13:45,718
And now? - Something completely
different.

153
00:13:45,807 --> 00:13:47,718
Watch this trick.

154
00:13:47,807 --> 00:13:51,766
Hold it on your head.

155
00:13:51,847 --> 00:13:55,078
What is this, Tomo? - Hold it
like this.

156
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:56,998
Put your arms down.

157
00:13:57,087 --> 00:13:59,237
Just great!

158
00:14:01,367 --> 00:14:03,403
Just watch this, Eso!

159
00:14:03,567 --> 00:14:04,966
What are you doing?

160
00:14:05,047 --> 00:14:06,400
Are you nuts?

161
00:14:06,807 --> 00:14:09,275
You crazy fucking idiot!

162
00:14:13,687 --> 00:14:15,439
Shit, I missed!

163
00:14:15,527 --> 00:14:17,404
I aimed for the forehead.

164
00:14:19,847 --> 00:14:23,476
Your turn now, tough guy!

165
00:14:24,727 --> 00:14:27,161
Fuck you! You're crazy!

166
00:14:27,247 --> 00:14:30,125
No problem, buddy. I'll play
the game.

167
00:14:31,527 --> 00:14:33,802
Here's your chance.

168
00:14:33,887 --> 00:14:38,199
I'm emptying the fucking gun! Relax.
A new player calls for fresh bullets.

169
00:14:38,287 --> 00:14:39,845
Eso, this isn't a joke.

170
00:14:39,927 --> 00:14:42,282
Relax, I've got experience.

171
00:14:45,167 --> 00:14:48,000
Uncle Faik bought some guns
cheap.

172
00:14:48,087 --> 00:14:49,202
We've been practicing.

173
00:14:49,287 --> 00:14:52,165
Buying guns now? - Your turn.

174
00:14:52,247 --> 00:14:54,317
Here's a moving target.

175
00:14:54,407 --> 00:14:56,602
Tomo, quit messing around.

176
00:14:56,687 --> 00:14:59,724
Milos, out of the way! - Goddam
you!

177
00:15:00,087 --> 00:15:01,759
Go ahead, shoot, tough guy!

178
00:15:01,847 --> 00:15:05,157
Milos, out of the way!

179
00:15:08,167 --> 00:15:10,840
Here we go!

180
00:15:17,487 --> 00:15:19,045
I don't give a fuck!

181
00:15:22,727 --> 00:15:26,117
If you survive, asshole,
I'll kill you!

182
00:15:34,887 --> 00:15:39,165
I gotta admit,
your uncle's really something.

183
00:15:46,247 --> 00:15:49,717
It's homemade. Have a swig.
It'll calm you down.

184
00:15:52,407 --> 00:15:54,159
We'll get a hunt going.

185
00:16:05,447 --> 00:16:08,325
She won't move.
She's lovesick.

186
00:16:08,407 --> 00:16:11,399
She's waiting for a train to
run her over

187
00:16:11,527 --> 00:16:14,121
Whose donkey is it?
It's Vujan's.

188
00:16:14,207 --> 00:16:17,483
Vujan who? - Vujan Peric from
Zabrdje.

189
00:16:17,567 --> 00:16:21,196
Vujan died five years ago!
But I spoke to him today.

190
00:16:26,647 --> 00:16:28,046
C'mon!

191
00:16:28,127 --> 00:16:30,163
Move!

192
00:16:30,247 --> 00:16:32,397
It's useless!

193
00:16:33,527 --> 00:16:35,324
Is she crying?

194
00:16:37,807 --> 00:16:39,923
I told you she's suffering.

195
00:16:43,447 --> 00:16:45,517
You don't know the secret word.

196
00:16:46,767 --> 00:16:48,837
Move it!

197
00:16:51,527 --> 00:16:53,404
Step aside.

198
00:17:04,607 --> 00:17:06,325
Now whistle.

199
00:17:19,407 --> 00:17:20,965
You're not listening to me.

200
00:17:25,767 --> 00:17:27,962
I don't say speed isn't
important.

201
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:30,481
But any fool can run fast.

202
00:17:30,567 --> 00:17:33,400
What are you talking about?

203
00:17:33,487 --> 00:17:36,524
Oh God, are You listening to
this?

204
00:17:36,607 --> 00:17:38,245
Sure, He's listening.

205
00:17:38,327 --> 00:17:41,444
Don't upset me, Nada. I never
said that.

206
00:17:41,527 --> 00:17:44,724
I said she looked at her husband
and saw he had big ears.

207
00:17:44,807 --> 00:17:47,275
Know how Napoleon won matches?

208
00:17:47,367 --> 00:17:49,085
You mean battles. - Right.

209
00:17:49,167 --> 00:17:50,441
He'd calculate how fast

210
00:17:50,527 --> 00:17:53,087
his cavalry could reach enemy
lines

211
00:17:53,167 --> 00:17:56,284
and cut them off. Speed's
everything!

212
00:17:56,407 --> 00:17:58,523
You read a lot,

213
00:17:58,607 --> 00:18:00,837
but careful you don't get a
headache.

214
00:18:00,927 --> 00:18:02,645
If you ride a cloud at the
speed of light

215
00:18:02,727 --> 00:18:05,764
you can't see yourself in a
mirror.

216
00:18:05,927 --> 00:18:08,077
I need that speed.

217
00:18:08,167 --> 00:18:09,964
Such speed's unhealthy.

218
00:18:10,047 --> 00:18:11,560
The feeling matters

219
00:18:11,647 --> 00:18:14,036
Know what feeling is? - Tell me.

220
00:18:14,127 --> 00:18:15,606
Talent.

221
00:18:15,687 --> 00:18:19,236
Talent? I'll make a note of it.

222
00:18:19,327 --> 00:18:21,443
You either have it or you don't.

223
00:18:22,007 --> 00:18:23,520
We were given reason

224
00:18:23,607 --> 00:18:25,359
to escape from our upsets

225
00:18:25,447 --> 00:18:27,517
and I'm really upset.

226
00:18:27,847 --> 00:18:30,315
I don't mean Anna Karenina,

227
00:18:31,567 --> 00:18:33,285
I mean me.

228
00:18:33,367 --> 00:18:35,517
I didn't come here for nothing,
you know.

229
00:18:35,607 --> 00:18:37,837
My next stop's the nursing home.

230
00:18:37,927 --> 00:18:40,122
I heard Luka talking to the
director,

231
00:18:40,207 --> 00:18:42,357
but he doesn't know I know.

232
00:18:42,447 --> 00:18:44,085
He told Luka: "No, Luka, please.

233
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:46,237
"It's too early for Jadranka

234
00:18:46,327 --> 00:18:48,204
"to enter a nursing home.
She'll still

235
00:18:48,287 --> 00:18:51,404
"young, so don't do it."

236
00:18:51,687 --> 00:18:53,917
But I worry for Milos!

237
00:18:54,007 --> 00:18:57,920
You know, a child without a
mother

238
00:18:58,007 --> 00:19:02,683
is like a broken umbrella in
the wind.

239
00:19:13,527 --> 00:19:15,677
Big fish eats little fish.

240
00:19:21,727 --> 00:19:23,479
God, what's wrong with me?

241
00:19:35,767 --> 00:19:37,519
I just want you to know:

242
00:19:37,607 --> 00:19:41,122
Never will I leave this place!
Ever!

243
00:19:41,207 --> 00:19:43,402
Come on, take a pill.

244
00:19:43,487 --> 00:19:47,036
Why don't you take it yourself?

245
00:19:47,127 --> 00:19:49,925
Think I don't know what you're
planning?

246
00:19:50,007 --> 00:19:52,237
Don't even think of it!

247
00:19:52,327 --> 00:19:55,524
You want your son to hear you?

248
00:20:04,847 --> 00:20:07,520
Lie down. Hospital regulations!

249
00:20:07,607 --> 00:20:10,758
Look, he won't let her on a
stretcher!

250
00:20:10,847 --> 00:20:13,680
Come on! - Please, listen to
me...

251
00:20:13,767 --> 00:20:17,396
I want to go home.

252
00:20:17,567 --> 00:20:20,240
I'd change that guy for free.

253
00:20:20,327 --> 00:20:22,397
Just one injection!

254
00:20:22,487 --> 00:20:24,478
His wife sings beautifully.

255
00:20:24,567 --> 00:20:25,716
I heard her on the radio.

256
00:20:25,807 --> 00:20:28,196
There's no nursing home.

257
00:20:28,287 --> 00:20:29,959
Too bad about the dust.

258
00:20:30,047 --> 00:20:31,162
She has an allergy?

259
00:20:31,247 --> 00:20:34,080
An allergy? She's out to lunch.

260
00:20:38,007 --> 00:20:39,759
That's what I call love.

261
00:20:41,647 --> 00:20:46,038
Wouldn't you like to be
carried like that in his arms?

262
00:20:46,127 --> 00:20:48,800
No way! He's not a Muslim.

263
00:20:48,887 --> 00:20:50,684
