536
00:42:16,527 --> 00:42:19,360
Me? What's wrong with you today?

537
00:42:19,487 --> 00:42:22,240
Veljo left a letter for Milos.

538
00:42:22,327 --> 00:42:24,318
It may be from Belgrade.

539
00:42:26,127 --> 00:42:27,719
On the table.

540
00:42:31,647 --> 00:42:33,160
From Belgrade.

541
00:42:33,287 --> 00:42:35,801
Maybe Partizan wants him.

542
00:42:36,807 --> 00:42:40,595
In today's events, one citizen
was killed

543
00:42:40,687 --> 00:42:42,917
and four wounded...

544
00:42:43,687 --> 00:42:49,000
He is to report within 24 hour
to his army unit.

545
00:42:49,127 --> 00:42:50,924
The army!

546
00:42:51,047 --> 00:42:53,641
That calls for a toast!

547
00:42:53,727 --> 00:42:55,763
It's the army, you idiot!

548
00:42:58,127 --> 00:43:02,996
Hey, Dad, if only you were here
to see Milos off to the army.

549
00:43:03,087 --> 00:43:06,762
Fuck you and your railroad!

550
00:43:06,847 --> 00:43:10,237
And damn me for letting you bring
me out here. What's wrong?

551
00:43:11,327 --> 00:43:14,876
What is it, woman? - What is
this?

552
00:43:17,807 --> 00:43:21,925
It's a scale model. - Scale
model?

553
00:43:23,087 --> 00:43:25,043
What are you doing?

554
00:43:25,167 --> 00:43:27,397
You call this a life?

555
00:43:29,087 --> 00:43:30,600
Calm down, woman!

556
00:43:30,727 --> 00:43:32,046
Let go of me!

557
00:43:34,607 --> 00:43:37,405
You call this a life? - Leave
that alone!

558
00:43:37,527 --> 00:43:41,281
You want a dead hero in the
house?

559
00:43:43,247 --> 00:43:48,002
Do you want to have a bust
made for your son?

560
00:43:48,127 --> 00:43:51,324
Idiot! It's not just military
service.

561
00:43:51,407 --> 00:43:54,365
Okay, calm down. - It's a call
to war.

562
00:43:54,487 --> 00:43:57,877
They won't get my child! - Leave
Dad alone

563
00:44:03,687 --> 00:44:05,518
I'm not going back!

564
00:44:09,047 --> 00:44:13,165
I won't go. - Wait!

565
00:44:15,087 --> 00:44:16,600
What is it now?

566
00:44:17,727 --> 00:44:19,206
Upset mother again?

567
00:44:19,287 --> 00:44:20,879
I didn't say a word.

568
00:44:20,967 --> 00:44:22,446
You did.

569
00:44:22,527 --> 00:44:23,926
So why's she crying?

570
00:44:24,007 --> 00:44:26,123
It wasn't me, honest.

571
00:44:26,247 --> 00:44:28,761
A Ramadan cake from Mom!

572
00:44:28,847 --> 00:44:30,599
Thanks, son.

573
00:44:30,687 --> 00:44:32,325
Off I go.

574
00:44:32,967 --> 00:44:35,606
Do you have a spark of
intelligence?

575
00:44:36,567 --> 00:44:39,320
Want to hear something
intelligent?

576
00:44:39,407 --> 00:44:42,319
Yes, tell us. - Come here.

577
00:44:43,687 --> 00:44:49,876
That manager, Zurovac, called.
He made me an official offer.

578
00:44:52,927 --> 00:44:55,646
They want your son to join
Partizan.

579
00:45:00,447 --> 00:45:03,405
Milos Djukic! - That's my boy!

580
00:45:04,567 --> 00:45:06,797
That's my boy!

581
00:45:06,887 --> 00:45:08,605
Milos!

582
00:45:21,847 --> 00:45:27,877
Tomo's got something for you!
Something fancy and modern!

583
00:45:46,127 --> 00:45:47,560
Basic training?

584
00:45:47,647 --> 00:45:49,877
Just basic training, honest!

585
00:45:50,007 --> 00:45:52,441
Filipovic arranged it with the
army.

586
00:45:52,527 --> 00:45:53,642
You can ask him.

587
00:45:53,727 --> 00:45:55,763
Milos!

588
00:45:55,967 --> 00:45:59,039
Hold on, son! Calm down!

589
00:45:59,167 --> 00:46:00,964
What is it?

590
00:46:02,407 --> 00:46:04,967
I don't believe him.

591
00:46:05,087 --> 00:46:07,726
Not a word he says!

592
00:46:07,967 --> 00:46:10,561
You have to do basic training.

593
00:46:10,647 --> 00:46:12,603
Not even God can change that.

594
00:46:12,687 --> 00:46:14,439
That's how it is.

595
00:46:14,527 --> 00:46:17,087
That's how it is? - Yes.

596
00:46:17,647 --> 00:46:19,285
How it is?

597
00:46:26,767 --> 00:46:31,795
As soon as you finish basic training,
you join Partizan straightaway.

598
00:46:32,647 --> 00:46:34,239
Listen to me.

599
00:46:34,407 --> 00:46:36,557
It's all been arranged.

600
00:46:39,207 --> 00:46:40,435
What's this?

601
00:46:45,247 --> 00:46:47,807
Why the long face if it's fine?

602
00:46:47,927 --> 00:46:49,758
Who has a long face?

603
00:46:51,767 --> 00:46:54,520
You know what I mean.

604
00:46:54,607 --> 00:46:57,167
What do you mean, long face?

605
00:46:59,967 --> 00:47:02,003
Just what I said.

606
00:47:02,087 --> 00:47:04,681
Why do you look so miserable?

607
00:47:05,887 --> 00:47:07,639
Miserable?

608
00:47:09,727 --> 00:47:11,206
Oh, son,

609
00:47:12,527 --> 00:47:14,643
I was born that way.

610
00:47:20,607 --> 00:47:21,801
Quick!

611
00:47:28,767 --> 00:47:32,999
Here's Tomo Krtolina,
your Santa Claus!

612
00:47:34,007 --> 00:47:36,965
Where have you been, Tomo?

613
00:47:37,127 --> 00:47:39,118
3, 4...

614
00:47:39,207 --> 00:47:44,122
Come one, come all

615
00:47:44,447 --> 00:47:47,120
Come everyone
When I take my oath this fall...

616
00:47:47,207 --> 00:47:49,198
Go to your mother now.

617
00:47:51,487 --> 00:47:53,079
Mother!

618
00:47:53,447 --> 00:47:54,880
Milos!

619
00:48:03,567 --> 00:48:05,637
Aleksic! - Hey, Luka...

620
00:48:05,767 --> 00:48:07,723
Old pal, where you been?

621
00:48:07,807 --> 00:48:10,799
I have to ask you something.
You're my only hope.

622
00:48:10,887 --> 00:48:13,003
Me, your only hope?

623
00:48:13,087 --> 00:48:17,877
If a soldier's your only hope
you're really in bad shape.

624
00:48:18,167 --> 00:48:21,239
It's about the war. She's
bugging me.

625
00:48:21,327 --> 00:48:25,115
She says he's going to war,
not basic training.

626
00:48:25,687 --> 00:48:27,598
There won't be a war.

627
00:48:27,727 --> 00:48:29,365
There won't?

628
00:48:29,447 --> 00:48:33,645
If everything goes according to plan,
we can avoid it.

629
00:48:34,207 --> 00:48:38,200
Auntie's little honeybunch!

630
00:48:43,087 --> 00:48:46,875
Where will you be stationed?
In Novi Sad. - That's not far!

631
00:48:46,967 --> 00:48:48,161
True.

632
00:48:48,247 --> 00:48:50,966
What's it near to? The battle
zone.

633
00:48:51,087 --> 00:48:54,477
You're as good at geography
as my old lady is.

634
00:48:55,207 --> 00:48:58,244
I've been halfway across Europe.

635
00:48:58,367 --> 00:49:00,722
Just eat. Eat!

636
00:49:33,367 --> 00:49:38,725
I have no one here. Just my son.
And my husband.

637
00:49:39,767 --> 00:49:41,644
Come over here.

638
00:49:42,327 --> 00:49:44,045
I have something to tell you.

639
00:49:58,927 --> 00:50:01,395
Oh, you're so funny!

640
00:50:01,487 --> 00:50:03,398
Our chief's in Moscow.

641
00:50:04,487 --> 00:50:06,239
If they let us,

642
00:50:06,327 --> 00:50:10,957
the military could take over,
and put an end to all this shit.

643
00:50:11,087 --> 00:50:13,555
That means no war?

644
00:50:15,007 --> 00:50:17,965
No war, Luka. - Thanks, Aleksic.

645
00:50:19,167 --> 00:50:20,839
You're a real brother.

646
00:50:20,967 --> 00:50:22,241
Sure, Luka.

647
00:50:28,607 --> 00:50:30,518
No war.

648
00:50:34,127 --> 00:50:36,163
Excuse me! Come over here.

649
00:50:36,247 --> 00:50:38,078
What is it? - Over here.

650
00:50:38,167 --> 00:50:40,840
C'mon, give me a little kiss.

651
00:50:41,407 --> 00:50:43,796
We won't have a war. - Says who?

652
00:50:43,887 --> 00:50:45,639
Someone who knows.

653
00:50:45,727 --> 00:50:49,436
That "someone" will end up
starting the war.

654
00:51:11,247 --> 00:51:14,478
Luka, you poor martyr.

655
00:51:14,567 --> 00:51:17,525
Fuck women and their creator!

656
00:51:25,447 --> 00:51:26,926
Stop playing!

657
00:51:28,087 --> 00:51:29,805
Stop the music!

658
00:51:31,367 --> 00:51:33,119
Stop, when I tell you.

659
00:51:33,407 --> 00:51:35,477
Is Milos serving in Hungary?

660
00:51:35,567 --> 00:51:37,364
Play one of our songs.

661
00:51:40,687 --> 00:51:41,961
Good evening.

662
00:51:42,047 --> 00:51:44,607
I wanna extend a welcome
to everyone here.

663
00:51:44,687 --> 00:51:50,364
And I'd like especially to welcome
the Djani Rebus Band.

664
00:51:50,447 --> 00:51:52,403
Give 'em a big hand!

665
00:51:54,327 --> 00:52:00,675
The song I'd like to dedicate to Milos
as he goes off to the army is "Time's Up"

666
00:52:00,807 --> 00:52:03,560
Karakaj. - Fuck Karakaj.

667
00:52:03,647 --> 00:52:05,080
Never Mind.

668
00:52:11,727 --> 00:52:16,562
Time's up!

669
00:52:16,887 --> 00:52:20,038
I have to go into the army

670
00:52:20,127 --> 00:52:22,880
So long, mom and dad

671
00:52:22,967 --> 00:52:26,164
So long, good old godfather

672
00:52:28,207 --> 00:52:32,917
So prepare my farewell party

673
00:52:34,527 --> 00:52:36,995
And now for the knockout punch!

674
00:52:38,327 --> 00:52:41,399
Momcilo! Momcilo!

675
00:52:43,087 --> 00:52:46,079
What is it now?

676
00:52:46,367 --> 00:52:49,598
The war's started. What are you
doing?

677
00:52:49,687 --> 00:52:51,518
What? What?

678
00:52:51,607 --> 00:52:54,041
The game's on, sweetpea.

679
00:52:54,127 --> 00:52:56,118
But I don't feel it!

680
00:53:14,287 --> 00:53:17,040
Gotcha, you slut!

681
00:53:21,407 --> 00:53:24,046
Godfather Rajko

682
00:53:24,127 --> 00:53:26,243
Let out the dog

683
00:53:27,167 --> 00:53:31,240
To watch over the house

684
00:53:32,327 --> 00:53:35,046
Don't let the wolf

685
00:53:35,127 --> 00:53:38,005
get his paws around

686
00:53:38,087 --> 00:53:41,079
my Red Riding Hood

687
00:53:41,167 --> 00:53:44,284
while I'm away

688
00:53:44,367 --> 00:53:48,679
County Tuzla, village of Karakaj

689
00:53:50,167 --> 00:53:54,797
That's the place I call home

690
00:54:47,807 --> 00:54:50,037
Anybody home?

691
00:54:54,247 --> 00:54:58,001
Anyone to see the soldier off?

692
00:54:58,447 --> 00:55:00,199
Here I am.

693
00:55:09,447 --> 00:55:10,960
Where's mother?

694
00:55:11,047 --> 00:55:13,686
I took her to the hospital.

695
00:55:13,767 --> 00:55:16,327
They're keeping her for tests.

696
00:55:19,047 --> 00:55:22,483
That allergy come pretty often?

697
00:55:22,567 --> 00:55:24,683
It doesn't go away so easily.

698
00:55:24,767 --> 00:55:28,077
In some cases, it's for life.

699
00:55:31,687 --> 00:55:34,565
Get ready. Don't just stand
there.

700
00:55:59,327 --> 00:56:00,919
I'll miss my bus.

701
00:56:01,007 --> 00:56:02,838
Wait!

702
00:56:03,847 --> 00:56:05,758
Kiss Mother for me.

703
00:56:18,447 --> 00:56:20,085
Wait up!

704
00:56:22,607 --> 00:56:24,438
Wait, Milos!

705
00:56:31,447 --> 00:56:34,917
You see? Speed is important.

706
00:56:35,927 --> 00:56:39,158
The feeling's important.
You dropped your wallet, dummy.

707
00:56:42,847 --> 00:56:45,486
Speed and feeling are equal.

708
00:56:46,047 --> 00:56:49,517
They're part of the same
equation.

709
00:56:52,807 --> 00:56:55,275
Take care.

710
00:57:19,887 --> 00:57:24,039
"Kiss Mother for me"

711
00:57:47,487 --> 00:57:49,523
Damn women!

712
00:58:46,167 --> 00:58:47,725
What?

713
00:58:48,927 --> 00:58:51,441
I'll put an end to your
babbling!

714
00:59:00,967 --> 00:59:05,722
Fuck you!

715
00:59:18,687 --> 00:59:22,282
Think what you want
but Veljo is no fool!

716
00:59:22,367 --> 00:59:23,959
Who says you are?

717
00:59:24,047 --> 00:59:26,163
When I use my head things clear
up.

718
00:59:26,247 --> 00:59:27,282
People told me:

719
00:59:27,367 --> 00:59:31,918
Veljo, hide your family! But I
didn't.

720
00:59:32,047 --> 00:59:33,685
Who told you to?

721
00:59:33,767 --> 00:59:37,316
I said: Luka's smart, an engineer.
He didn't hide his wife.

722
00:59:37,407 --> 00:59:39,523
So why should I? - What?

723
00:59:39,607 --> 00:59:41,916
You hid her with the Hungarian.

724
00:59:42,007 --> 00:59:45,124
I told my wife: Off to Serbia
with you!

725
00:59:45,247 --> 00:59:47,203
I didn't hide Jadranka.

726
00:59:47,287 --> 00:59:50,802
But I saw her leave with the
Hungarian.

727
01:00:04,287 --> 01:00:08,246
Listen good,
the railroad is under military control.

728
01:00:08,367 --> 01:00:12,599
From now on, you answer only to
us.

729
01:00:12,807 --> 01:00:16,880
You're in charge of maintenance
and communications.

730
01:00:16,967 --> 01:00:19,276
Report all damage to me.

731
01:00:19,367 --> 01:00:20,846
That's an order.

732
01:00:20,927 --> 01:00:24,806
The tracks must be operational
at all times. Understand?

733
01:00:46,967 --> 01:00:50,084
Look at her! Where are you
going?

734
01:00:50,207 --> 01:00:52,437
Want a train to run you over?

735
01:00:52,527 --> 01:00:54,245
Go on home!

736
01:00:54,327 --> 01:00:56,966
It's useless to talk to you!

737
01:00:57,527 --> 01:00:59,245
What did you bring?

738
01:00:59,327 --> 01:01:01,363
A bit of everything.

739
01:01:01,447 --> 01:01:02,960
What goes into a Bosnian stew?

740
01:01:03,047 --> 01:01:06,164
Everything. Milos loves it.

741
01:01:06,247 --> 01:01:08,602
Hear those explosions?

742
01:01:16,927 --> 01:01:18,246
They're pounding away.

743
01:01:18,327 --> 01:01:20,124
Milos is being transferred here.

744
01:01:20,207 --> 01:01:22,846
Whereabouts? - To Bosnia.

745
01:01:22,967 --> 01:01:26,357
He'll pop in if he's nearby.

746
01:01:26,447 --> 01:01:28,642
I'm scared to be in my house
alone.

747
01:01:28,727 --> 01:01:33,642
I brought a chess set. We can
have a game. Good idea.

748
01:01:35,567 --> 01:01:37,398
What's that?

749
01:01:42,967 --> 01:01:45,037
They're our boys.

750
01:01:46,207 --> 01:01:47,879
Hey, soldier!

751
01:01:53,847 --> 01:01:56,680
Those aren't our boys! Run!

752
01:01:57,007 --> 01:01:59,567
Didn't I say they were pounding
away?

753
01:02:00,487 --> 01:02:02,284
What is it? Not afraid?

754
01:02:02,367 --> 01:02:04,927
Why afraid? They announced a
cease-fire.

755
01:02:05,007 --> 01:02:06,486
A cease-fire?

756
01:02:07,567 --> 01:02:09,398
Fucking cease-fire!

757
01:02:11,407 --> 01:02:12,886
They're pounding away!

758
01:02:16,287 --> 01:02:17,925
I can't hear anything.

759
01:02:31,327 --> 01:02:33,158
You have the first move.

760
01:02:34,407 --> 01:02:37,524
I'm black. - Fine.

761
01:02:47,527 --> 01:02:49,324
Know what my old man used to
say?

762
01:02:49,407 --> 01:02:50,556
What?

763
01:02:52,047 --> 01:02:54,436
That war always comes quickly.

764
01:02:54,527 --> 01:02:56,722
You see it coming.

765
01:02:56,807 --> 01:02:58,399
It rolls in like a flood,

766
01:02:58,487 --> 01:03:02,196
but starts
by surprise, understand? - Yeah.

767
01:03:15,447 --> 01:03:17,915
Let's play, and the hell with
them.

768
01:03:22,567 --> 01:03:23,602
Veljo!

769
01:03:24,887 --> 01:03:27,117
Was that a 120mm shell? - Yes.

770
01:03:27,247 --> 01:03:28,965
Where'd the Ustasha get them?

771
01:03:29,047 --> 01:03:31,402
Genscher sent 'em to the Croats.

772
01:03:39,167 --> 01:03:42,364
Wake up, Luka! - What are you
yelling for?

773
01:03:42,967 --> 01:03:45,640
Where's Veljo? He's not home.

774
01:03:45,727 --> 01:03:47,763
Why do you need him?

775
01:03:54,247 --> 01:03:56,715
Mobilization!

776
01:03:59,207 --> 01:04:01,767
A rocket launcher consists the
following:

777
01:04:01,847 --> 01:04:05,362
The barrel, the rocket inside,

778
01:04:06,567 --> 01:04:08,876
front and rear sights,

779
01:04:08,967 --> 01:04:10,764
and the launch mechanism.

780
01:04:10,847 --> 01:04:11,962
Is that clear?

781
01:04:13,287 --> 01:04:15,084
You, young man.

782
01:04:16,207 --> 01:04:17,481
Step forward.

783
01:04:19,007 --> 01:04:21,043
What in thunderation!

784
01:04:25,047 --> 01:04:27,117
We'll do a little test shot.

785
01:04:27,207 --> 01:04:31,485
See that isolated tree at 250
meters?

786
01:04:31,687 --> 01:04:33,245
That's the target.

787
01:04:34,447 --> 01:04:37,041
Okay, doll, is that clear?

788
01:04:37,127 --> 01:04:38,924
It is.

789
01:04:39,647 --> 01:04:41,319
Take aim...

790
01:04:45,847 --> 01:04:47,041
Fire!

791
01:04:55,767 --> 01:04:58,565
Zowie! What a ricochet!

792
01:05:15,087 --> 01:05:17,476
Good news, your son's here!

793
01:05:17,567 --> 01:05:19,239
Milos! Where?

794
01:05:19,327 --> 01:05:21,761
At the house. The captain drove
him there

795
01:05:24,007 --> 01:05:25,725
Is that the truth?

796
01:05:25,847 --> 01:05:27,997
Why would I lie?

797
01:05:50,127 --> 01:05:51,685
Milos!

798
01:06:06,007 --> 01:06:07,645
Get down, Zujka!

799
01:07:31,167 --> 01:07:35,843
Why are you lying like this?
Stretch out.

800
01:08:30,367 --> 01:08:31,766
Wait up!

801
01:08:50,807 --> 01:08:53,958
Take it easy! Don't overdo it!

802
01:08:56,807 --> 01:08:59,196
Where's my Milos hiding?

803
01:09:18,927 --> 01:09:20,406
Hey, Veljo!

804
01:09:23,927 --> 01:09:25,804
Everything okay at your place?

805
01:09:27,047 --> 01:09:30,005
It really shook last night.

806
01:09:30,087 --> 01:09:33,796
I lost some roof tiles.
You know the real miracle,

807
01:09:33,887 --> 01:09:37,846
nothing happened to the Bosnian stew.
It just got cold.

808
01:09:39,127 --> 01:09:41,163
Oh, my Luka!

809
01:09:41,287 --> 01:09:44,723
My boy visits and I give him
nothing.

810
01:09:44,807 --> 01:09:47,367
What an ass, I fell asleep.

811
01:09:52,447 --> 01:09:54,165
Had any damage?

812
01:09:54,247 --> 01:09:56,442
Come down. I have news.

813
01:09:56,527 --> 01:10:01,840
Could you hand me up that long board,
there, on the ledge?

814
01:10:10,927 --> 01:10:14,397
Come down. I have to tell you
something.

815
01:10:15,767 --> 01:10:17,883
I can't. Tell me.

816
01:10:18,087 --> 01:10:21,966
Come down!
It's not about Jadranka.

817
01:10:23,167 --> 01:10:24,759
Is it Milos?

818
01:10:31,287 --> 01:10:32,879
Is he dead?

819
01:10:34,807 --> 01:10:37,605
Tell me. Is he wounded?

820
01:10:38,807 --> 01:10:40,684
No. Come down!

821
01:10:40,767 --> 01:10:42,519
Tell me what happened?

822
01:10:42,607 --> 01:10:45,838
I'll murder you if I come down!

823
01:10:48,607 --> 01:10:50,404
He's a prisoner.

824
01:10:50,927 --> 01:10:52,565
A prisoner?

825
01:10:53,847 --> 01:10:55,803
Milos, a prisoner?

826
01:11:04,887 --> 01:11:05,922
How did it happen?

827
01:11:06,007 --> 01:11:07,679
The captain will tell you.

828
01:11:18,967 --> 01:11:22,926
Vladan! Get the chopper for the wounded!
On the double!

829
01:11:27,887 --> 01:11:29,400
Captain!

830
01:11:34,247 --> 01:11:38,365
Send your unit to hill 805!

831
01:11:38,647 --> 01:11:41,719
He wants to take Milos's place.

832
01:11:41,807 --> 01:11:43,798
To do what? - To replace Milos.

833
01:11:43,887 --> 01:11:45,479
Transfer me!

834
01:11:45,767 --> 01:11:47,485
You've gone crazy too?

835
01:11:47,727 --> 01:11:50,605
Let's go home. - I don't want to.

836
01:11:55,567 --> 01:11:56,920
Listen.

837
01:11:57,047 --> 01:12:00,278
I won't leave without a mission.

838
01:12:09,567 --> 01:12:14,083
Remember, this isn't your
private war.

839
01:12:14,727 --> 01:12:18,322
I can't take any more. I'll
kill myself.

840
01:12:19,527 --> 01:12:21,165
What?

841
01:12:23,607 --> 01:12:26,883
Vladan, get out. - You haven't
finished.

842
01:12:26,967 --> 01:12:28,446
Get out. - But you haven't...

843
01:12:28,527 --> 01:12:30,597
Dismissed! - Yes, sir.

844
01:12:35,487 --> 01:12:37,159
You'll kill yourself?

845
01:12:38,407 --> 01:12:42,036
Too easy. Death doesn't hurt,
my friend.

846
01:12:43,247 --> 01:12:45,681
It's living that hurts.

847
01:12:47,887 --> 01:12:49,923
Did you know I have a brother?

848
01:12:50,167 --> 01:12:52,556
Or I had one. I don't know.

849
01:12:52,647 --> 01:12:54,603
My Stevan.

850
01:12:55,887 --> 01:12:57,605
It's been two years.

851
01:12:58,607 --> 01:13:00,757
Two years since he disappeared.

852
01:13:02,927 --> 01:13:04,838
He's not among the dead

853
01:13:05,327 --> 01:13:07,397
so I can't bury him.

854
01:13:07,487 --> 01:13:09,682
He's not among the prisoners.

855
01:13:09,767 --> 01:13:10,722
He's not among the living

856
01:13:10,807 --> 01:13:12,399
so I can't hug him.

857
01:13:12,487 --> 01:13:14,364
The man simply vanished!

858
01:13:14,487 --> 01:13:17,524
Vanished into thin air!

859
01:13:17,647 --> 01:13:20,036
I asked for a transfer to Lika.

860
01:13:20,127 --> 01:13:22,277
Know what they told me?

861
01:13:24,567 --> 01:13:27,001
This isn't my private war.

862
01:13:27,727 --> 01:13:29,240
It's someone's war, my dear
Luka.

863
01:13:32,647 --> 01:13:34,000
It's a war for scum.

864
01:13:35,887 --> 01:13:37,286
Not yours or mine, for sure.

865
01:13:42,887 --> 01:13:46,197
We have good reason to believe
that Milos is alive.

866
01:13:48,607 --> 01:13:50,598
We'll find him.

867
01:13:51,087 --> 01:13:53,317
We'll liberate him.

868
01:13:55,447 --> 01:13:57,563
Know how big my Stevan is?

869
01:13:57,927 --> 01:13:59,838
Three times my size.

